<div>		



<span class="section_title">HOTTEST CE PRODUCTS AND TECHNOLOGIES TO BE SHOWCASED AT CES UNVEILED: THE OFFICIAL PRESS EVENT OF CES</span>

<br><br>		
<strong><i>Arlington, Virginia&nbsp;-&nbsp;6/15/2006</i></strong>
<br><br>
The hottest products and technologies from 80 leading consumer technology companies will be on display at the third annual CES Unveiled: The Official Press Event of the International CES<sup>&#174</sup>, on Saturday, January 6, 2007. The 2007 International CES, the world's largest consumer technology tradeshow, returns to Las Vegas, January 8-11, 2007 for its 40th anniversary celebration. 
<p>
      CES Unveiled provides media and analysts an exclusive opportunity to preview the latest products emerging on the market and network with the industry's top technology companies, two days before the show floor officially opens. In addition to exclusive tabletop exhibits, press also will get a sneak preview of the prestigious International CES Innovations Design and Engineering Honorees showcase, which will be displayed at the event.
<p>
      "Moving into its third year, CES Unveiled has become the premier sneak peek into the hot products and technologies that will take the industry by storm at the 2007 International CES," said Karen Chupka, senior vice president of conferences and events for the Consumer Electronics Association (CEA<sup>&#174</sup>), producer of the International CES. "The exclusive exhibits, coupled with the Innovations honorees and great networking opportunities, make Unveiled a must-attend CES event." 
<p>
      Building upon the successful launch of the Innovations Plus at the Sands in 2006, CES Unveiled again will return to the Sands Expo and Convention Center/The Venetian for the 2007 event. Also new to The Venetian for the 2007 International CES are the high-performance audio and home theater exhibits. Falling under one CES product category, more than 200 high-performance audio and home theater exhibitors will now take advantage of the increased space at the Sands and The Venetian, allowing for the ultimate demonstration experience for exhibitors and attendees. 
<p>
      CES Unveiled will take place on January 6, 2007, from 4:00-7:00 p.m. at the Sands/The Venetian, Marco Polo Ballroom. Media and analysts can pick up their badge and registration materials immediately prior to the event at special registration kiosks at the lower level of the Sands/The Venetian. Only credentialed media and analysts will be allowed into the event.
<p>
      Media and analysts may register for CES Unveiled when registering for the 2007 International CES at <a href="http://www.CESweb.org/press">www.CESweb.org/press</a>, beginning July 6. For more news on CES before, during and after the show, visit <a href="http://www.CESweb.org">www.CESweb.org</a>, the interactive source for CES information. Beyond registration, attendees can make their hotel and travel arrangements through <a href="http://www.CESweb.org">www.CESweb.org</a>. International guests can obtain help in applying for travel visas via the website as well.
<p>
       Note to Journalists:  Detailed press conference information will be available later this year. Journalists are encouraged to arrive in Las Vegas by Saturday, January 6 to take advantage of all the CES press events.
<p>      
<b>About CEA:</b><br>
&#160&#160&#160&#160&#160The Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) is the preeminent trade association promoting growth in the consumer technology industry through technology policy, events, research, promotion and the fostering of business and strategic relationships.  CEA represents more than 2,100 corporate members involved in the design, development, manufacturing, distribution and integration of audio, video, mobile electronics, wireless and landline communications, information technology, home networking, multimedia and accessory products, as well as related services that are sold through consumer channels. Combined, CEA's members account for more than $125 billion in annual sales.  CEA's resources are available online at <a href="http://www.ce.org">www.CE.org</a>, the definitive source for information about the consumer electronics industry.<br>
&#160&#160&#160&#160&#160CEA also sponsors and manages the International CES - Defining Tomorrow's Technology.  All profits from CES are reinvested into industry services, including technical training and education, industry promotion, engineering standards development, market research and legislative advocacy.
<br><br>
Attachment:&nbsp;<a target="new" href="http://www.ce.org/shared_files/pr_attachments/Unveiled Release.doc">CES UNVEILED: THE OFFICIAL PRESS EVENT OF CES</a>

